<define-tag pagetitle>bind</define-tag>
<define-tag report_date>1999-11-16</define-tag>
<define-tag packages>bind</define-tag>
<define-tag description>Denial of service vulnerabilities in bind</define-tag>
<define-tag isvulnerable>yes</define-tag>
<define-tag fixed>yes</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>The version of bind in Debian GNU/Linux 2.1 is vulnerable
to several denial of service attacks, as outlined in CERT advisory CA-99.14.
Note that the bind in Debian GNU/Linux 2.1 (bind 8.2.1) is <em>not</em>
vulnerable to the NXT record root exploit, which takes advantage of a feature
added to bind 8.2.</define-tag>

